-- Copper Futures Decline on Comex in New York, Erases Earlier Gain of 1.2%
-- Steve Stroth
-- 2010-07-15T14:18:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/copper-futures-decline-on-comex-in-new-york-erases-earlier-gain-of-1-2-.html

          
          
             Copper futures for September
delivery fell 0.85 cent, or 0.3 percent, to $3 a pound at 10:18
a.m. on the Comex in New York. Earlier, the contract gained as
much as 1.2 percent.  
          
          


  


        